{# ── WHAT IT IS · TL;DR prose. #qb-support-independent-tldr-body speakable id preserved. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-independent-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">What independent QuickBooks help actually is.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose"><p id="qb-support-independent-tldr-body">{{ tldr | safe }}</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE FIX THAT INTUIT WON'T/CAN'T · r-3 dc-cards. The accounting INSIDE your own
     file — not the software, not the account. Each card routes to a built spoke where one exists. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-independent-fixes" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Inside your own file</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">What we fix that Intuit&rsquo;s support won&rsquo;t &mdash; or can&rsquo;t.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:70ch;">Intuit supports the product and your account. None of that touches the accounting <em>inside</em> your file &mdash; the numbers, the history, the structure. That is exactly where these problems live, and it is what an independent ProAdvisor firm is for.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for f in fixes %}
      {%- if f.href %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ f.href }}">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ f.eyebrow | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ f.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
        <span class="hub-card__go">{{ f.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span>
      </a>
      {%- else %}
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ f.eyebrow | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ f.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── HOW THE ENGAGEMENT WORKS · process-grid (three phases). ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-independent-process">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How it works</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Free review, written scope, a named ProAdvisor.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:70ch;">No mystery, no open-ended hourly meter. The path from &ldquo;something&rsquo;s wrong in my file&rdquo; to a fixed-fee fix is the same every time.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="process-step__n">{{ p.when | safe }}</div>
        <h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p>{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FIXED-FEE FRAMING · canonical pricing only (no hourly, no invented figures). checklist
     in dc-card. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-independent-pricing" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Fixed fee, scoped in writing</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">What it costs.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Every engagement is a fixed fee agreed in writing before any work starts &mdash; no hourly surprises. The free file review is what sets the number; the ranges below are the typical bands the scope lands in.</p>
    <div class="dc-card">
      <ul class="checklist" id="qb-support-independent-pricing-list">
        {%- for tier in pricing %}
        <li><strong>{{ tier.name | safe }} &mdash; {{ tier.range | safe }}.</strong> {{ tier.body | safe }}</li>
        {%- endfor %}
      </ul>
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:14px;">Ranges are typical, not quotes. Your written fixed-fee scope follows the free file review. Fees cover the accounting work inside your own QuickBooks file; they do not include Intuit subscription or product costs, which you pay Intuit directly.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CALM CTA · the paid independent lane (calm dc-card, btn-cta + data-ga). ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-independent-breakout">
